Shulk (Xenoblade Chronicles)
Weapon type: Unique
Crystal Color: Red
Spheres: A B D

A note on Shulk: His skills change. A lot. His base game mechanics are hard to translate perfectly into DFFOO format so I did the
best I could. His flowchart is gonna end up like Alisae's or worse

Skill 1: Back Slash
Back Slash:
 1-hit Melee BRV+HP attack.
 Greatly increases BRV damage dealt when attacking enemies not targeting self.
 Fills Talent Gauge by 20%.
 Becomes Monado Art: Buster when [Activate Monado] is active.
Monado Art: Buster
 3-hit AoE Melee BRV+ST HP attack.
 Greatly increases BRV damage dealt to Machine-type enemies.
 Uses: 6
15cp: Replica Monado
 +
c.55: Back Slash Extend
 +Adds 3 uses
Back Slash:
 +Becomes a 4-hit Melee BRV+HP attack
 +Greatly increases BRV potency

Talent Gauge:
An overhead gauge that fills much like an EX recast gauge.
Once Talent Gauge reaches 100%, turns into special effect [Activate Monado] for 3 turns.
[Activate Monado]: Critical Hit Rate Up (100%), Critical Hit Damage Up (100%)
                   All BRV damage ignores DEF

Skill 2: Stream Edge
Stream Edge: 
 Breaks all enemies, if not already Broken.
 AoE Melee HP attack.
 Deals 100% HP damage to all enemies.
 Fills Talent Gauge by 50%.
 Becomes Monado Art: Cyclone when [Activate Monado] is active.
Monado Art: Cyclone
 2-hit AoE Melee BRV+HP attack.
 Deals 100% HP damage to all enemies.
 Greatly increases BRV damage dealt to Machine-type enemies.
 Uses: 4
35cp: Monado Agni
 +
c.60: Stream Edge Extend
 +Adds 4 uses
Stream Edge:
 +Becomes a 4-hit AoE Melee BRV+HP attack
 +Allows for 120% Stolen BRV overflow
 +Resets enemy Break status before Breaking enemies
Monado Art: Cyclone
 +Becomes a 5-hit AoE Melee BRV+HP attack
 +Allows for 120% Stolen BRV overflow
 +
 
Put any buff/debuff descriptions or brv/hp+ variants here
 
EX: Monado
 +Equips EX ability Shaker Edge
Shaker Edge:
 4-hit Melee BRV+HP attack.
 Allows for 120% Stolen BRV overflow.
 Grants [Shadow Eye] to self for 2 turns after use.
 Fills Talent Gauge by 20%.
 Becomes Monado Art: Purge when [Activate Monado] is active.
Monado Art: Purge
 5-hit Melee BRV+HP attack.
 Greatly increases BRV damage dealt to Machine-type enemies.
 Allows for 150% Stolen BRV overflow.
 Inflicts [Aura Seal] on target for 2 turns.
 Grants [Vision] to self for 2 turns.
Recast: Slightly Slow
  -LB1:
  -LB2:
  -LB3:
 EX+:
  -LB1:
  -LB2:
  -LB3:

[Shadow Eye]: ATK Up (50%)
              Prevents enemies from targeting self
[Aura Seal]: Prevents enemies from affecting player party with aura effects.
             Does not prevent aura effects that target self or allies.
[Vision]: Evasion Rate Up (50%)
          When self or an ally is about to take fatal damage, Shulk intercepts with a free turn in which his skills change
Light Heal: Replaces BRV Attack.
            Heals an ally for 15% of their Max HP.
Monado Art: Shield: Replaces HP Attack.
                    Grants [Monado Shield] to all allies for 1 turn.
Monado Art: Speed: Replaces Back Slash/Monado Art: Buster.
                   Does not consume skill usage.
                   Grants [Monado Speed] to one ally for 1 turn.
Monado Art: Armor: Replaces Stream Edge/Monado Art: Cyclone.
                   Does not consume skill usage.
                   Grants [Monado Armor] to all allies for 1 turn.
[Monado Shield]: Blocks HP damage based on own INT BRV (50%).
[Monado Speed]: Evasion Rate Up (100%)
[Monado Armor]: PHY Damage Reduction (60%)
                MAG Damage Reduction (60%)

LD: True Monado
+Equips LD ability Monado Art: Eater
 3-hit AoE Melee BRV+ST HP attack, triggered twice.
 Gain BRV based on (20% of) HP damage dealt after both HP attacks.
 Greatly increases BRV damage dealt to Machine-type enemies.
 Deals 50% splash HP damage to non-targets.
 Dispels all enemy buffs, including framed buffs.
 Fills Talent Gauge to 100% and activates [Activate Monado] before BRV hits.
 Inflicts [Bleed] on all targets for 6 turns.
 Uses: 2
  -LB1:
  -LB2:
  -LB3:
  
[Bleed]: Poison (20% target Max BRV)
         Deals HP damage by 80% of Attack (will not reduce HP below 1)
